MEDIA personality Ayanda Thabethe has a bun in the oven. The TV presenter announced her pregnancy with a video where she can be seen be seen cradling her baby bump on sand dunes. “More than my heart can hold. Greater than I deserve. Beyond everything I could ask for. An answer to a secret and nervous prayer. Finally, my forever has come,” she said captioning the video of herself that is accompanied by the soothing sounds of Frank Ocean’s hit song Goodspeed. Shortly after sharing the good news that she is pregnant, congratulatory messages flooded in for the model and presenter and industry colleagues such as Lasizwe, Zola Nombona, Rich Mnisi and Mihlali Ndamase were among the long list of people who wished her well. ALSO READ | TEARY LANCOCO SHARES ABOUT ZUMA SPLIT “Congratulations beautiful. So, so happy for you!” said Ntando Kunene. While Lerato Kganyago said: “It was hard keeping this secret. My heart still jumps for joy for you and the baby. My YaYa.” It is yet unclear who Ayanda’s baby daddy is as the model has kept her private life away from prying eyes after previous relationships. Ayanda was previously married to Andile Ncube and also dated rapper Zulu Mkhathini. A post shared by @ayandathabethe_ 